       Change Summary Explanation
       FY2027 funding was increased by $513.308 million:

       - $203.551 million was realigned from PE 0605414N to better align all Unmanned Carrier Aviation funding to one PE
       - $261.494 million increased to fund program of record identified gaps in MQ-25 requirements for Obsolescence, Cyber, Test and UMCS MD-5 software
       development requirements
       - $64.933 million increased to start the development efforts for Stingray "To the Fight"
       - $16.670 million decreased for rate/miscellaneous adjustments

       PU 3278: FY2027 funding increased by $440.297 million from the FY26 President's Budget Request. $186.829 million was realigned from PE 0605414N to
       better align all Unmanned Carrier Aviation funding to one PE, fund Program identified gaps in MQ-25 Obsolescence, Cyber and Test requirements ($251.252
       million), funding to start the development efforts for Stingray "To the Fight" ($64.933 million), realignment of funding to UMCS PU 3279 to continue GCS software
       development and integration (-$48.000 million), and rate/miscellaneous adjustments (-$14.717 million).

       PU 3279: FY2027 funding request was increased by $73.011 million from the FY26 President's Budget Request. $16.722 million was realigned from PE
       0605414N to better align all Unmanned Carrier Aviation funding to one PE, continue GCS software development and integration ($48.000 million), fund Program
       identified gaps in Unmanned Control Station (UMCS) MD-5 requirements ($10.242 million), and rate/miscellaneous adjustments (-$1.953 million).

