A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The scope of the program includes, but is not limited to, system level requirements identification, allocation of requirements to segments and components, design,
development, integration, fabrication, test, training, and support activities to provide the MQ-25 capabilities. To provide these capabilities, MQ-25 will transition
technologies from other programs and adapt them into the carrier environment. MQ-25 will deliver the necessary air vehicles, command, control, connectivity, shipboard
and land-based launch and recovery control systems, associated support systems, interfaces, and upgrades to other Navy systems (as required) to meet the required
capabilities.

