- Continue integration, operational assessment, and implementation of SRA for FoSUAS platforms.
- Continue to perform NDAA sections 817 (FY2023) and 848 (FY2020) Compliance testing on systems;
Cybersecurity and NDAA compliance testing is performed by a third-party vendor to ensure appropriate levels for
data encryption, implementation of multi-factor authentication, and risk assessments.
- Continue assessment of UAS, software applications, payload/sensor capabilities, and other UAS ancillary
components.
- Refine CDS integration alternatives.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
- Conduct System Readiness Assessments (SRAs) and evaluate emerging UAS platforms, software, payloads,
and ancillary components for the Family of Small UAS (FoSUAS).
- Perform third-party cybersecurity and compliance testing to meet National Defense Authorization Act (NDAA)
and DoW drone policy requirements.
- Test and validate M-Code GPS, 5G/LTE, anti-jamming, and SATCOM capabilities to ensure resilient Beyond-
Line-of-Sight (BLOS) operations in contested environments.
- Execute operational testing with Organic Precision Fires (OPF) to measure Target Location Error (TLE) and
validate system lethality.
- Assess advanced tactics including swarming, marsupial employment, and system performance in Counter-UAS
(C-UAS) scenarios.
- Validate Unmanned Common Controller (UCC) interoperability and conduct maritime testing to ensure systems
are effective aboard USMC vessels.

