FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The increase in Test & Evaluation from FY2026 to FY2027 increase enables a critical shift from basic
sustainment testing to a comprehensive, operationally focused evaluation required to prove the system meets
the advanced performance parameters of the CDD. This funds a robust test architecture to validate system
lethality, survivability, and interoperability in threat-representative scenarios. Key activities enabled by this
increase include kinetic testing/certifications, performance validation in GPS-denied and contested spectrum
environments, and operational assessments of advanced capabilities like swarming and C-UAS resilience.
