       Change Summary Explanation
       The increase from FY 2026 to FY 2027 directly supports Presidential and Secretary of War priorities to innovate, modernize, and expand our inventory of small
       Unmanned Aircraft Systems (sUAS). This investment ensures the Marine Corps can meet urgent battlefield needs and maintain a technological advantage
       against near-peer adversaries. Funding will be utilized to aggressively pivot from sustainment-level funding to a targeted development effort designed to close
       critical capability gaps identified in the CDD, develop and demonstrate high-priority technologies, including expeditionary power, Beyond-Line-of-Sight (BLOS)
       communications, and an interoperable common controller and conduct comprehensive operational testing to validate system lethality, survivability against C-UAS
       threats, and effectiveness in contested electromagnetic spectrum environments. This funding enables the program to formally prove that these new systems meet
       the demanding requirements for the future fight.




