Description: This activity provides leadership and essential planning, program and financial management,
and execution of NMSO efforts as well as coordination with the other Services, the Office of Secretary of War
(OSW), the Joint Staff, and other agencies. It also oversees initiatives to develop, promulgate, and track the
policies and procedures necessary to support the creation of a robust and credible capability to create synthetic
environments, accurately represent platforms and systems, predict outcomes, and provide inputs to Naval
decision-makers and operational users.

These core services support the DoN and Navy-wide M&S alignment, planning, and execution, as well as
NMSO's community services and community experiments and prototypes. It oversees the generation and
application of M&S and VV&A policy, standards, guidance, and codes of best practice. It also provides guidance
on documenting M&S support plans, capability summaries, and associated data in a way that is discoverable
and reusable.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue to provide leadership, outreach, and engagement to promote the efficient and effective application of
M&S policy standards, best practices, and associated technologies to improve the use and reuse of M&S across
the Navy Enterprise

- Continue to develop and implement DoN and Navy M&S policy and Strategic Guidance and support the
creation and implementation of M&S Community Road Maps and Implementation Plans.

- Continue to work across the DoN, DoW, and other Services and Agencies to develop M&S Standards and
promulgate implementing policy to support cross-program and cross-service interoperability.

- Continue to plan, align, manage, and monitor the financial status of NMSO core services, community services,
and community experiments and prototypes.

- Initiate synchronization of M&S R&D, S&T, Engineering, and MBSE to maximize unity of effort across the Navy
and leverage associated initiatives across DoW, industry, and academia.
