FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue to develop, promulgate, and monitor the use of Navy M&S plans, templates, standards, VV&A
handbooks, M&S procurement guidance, and similar.

- Continue to provide M&S community-wide services and digital environments (like Leveraging Innovations,
Frameworks and Technologies [LIFT]) as well as digital engineering capabilities (e.g., the Naval Integrated
Modeling Environment (N-IME)) to support discoverability and model reuse.

- Continue to support the collaboration of Navy M&S subject matter experts (SMEs), working groups, and
technical exchanges to implement M&S guidance, standards, VV&A, education, and reuse within their
communities and to increase awareness of reusable M&S products, processes, and standards.

- Continue enhancing the interactions between NMSO and the MOVES program and support a broader
collaboration to enable the effective definition of research topics and the application of associated results.

