Title: COMMUNITY EXPERIMENTS and PROTOTYPES                                                                                  6.731       6.227       7.900      0.000         7.900
                                                                                                            Articles:           -           -           -          -             -
Description: This activity develops and executes experiments and prototypes focused on the advancement of
M&S capabilities and technologies to increase M&S efficiency and effectiveness in its application across the
Navy Enterprise. It supports project prototypes and experiments to help determine the feasibility and applicability
of innovative technical approaches, employment concepts, and proposed standards within Navy M&S. It also
investigates Service-unique requirements to achieve M&S efficiency, effectiveness, and interoperability. It
develops prototype tools designed to improve the access and use of operationally relevant M&S products
to support Navy warfare assessments, and acquisition requirements. This activity focuses on supporting
Navy acquisition and warfighting priorities like the seamless incorporation of enterprise engineering in M&S
applications. Individual efforts focus on developing capabilities to optimize assessment and acquisition functional
and mission objectives through more efficient development and use of M&S.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue to make improvements in the ability to model and simulate threat systems that span application areas
across force level analysis, high fidelity applications, digital engineering applications, and test and evaluation and
that include data from both the intelligence community and engineering derivations and extensions.

- Continue Prototyping means, methods, and processes that apply artificial intelligence and/or machine learning
to enhance simulation applications, simulation environments, and simulation federations.

- Continue the development of M&S capabilities to efficiently examine all domain warfighting capabilities and
concepts to advanced system, system of systems, and family of systems maritime warfighting capabilities.

- Continue to extend enhancements in cross-system and cross-service Live, Virtual, and Constructive (LVC)
simulation interoperability and interface capabilities.



