INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$0708730N$$, 2027, $$The Advanced Shipyard Technology (AST) seeks to improve the productivity, quality, and reduce costs of maintenance performed by the Navy public shipyards. The
resulting technologies developed by this program benefit both the naval shipyard and the US Navy.$$, $$The Advanced Shipyard Technology (AST) program supports Navy efforts to address warfighter maintenance and construction challenges by developing, maturing,
and demonstrating technologies that improve Naval Shipyard sustainment operations. AST aligns with priorities outlined in the CNO Navigation Plan 2025, which
emphasizes improving fleet readiness and accelerating the integration of robotics, autonomy, and digital capabilities across Navy operational and sustainment
environments.

AST funding facilitates collaboration between government, academia, and industry to rapidly prototype and transition technology and process improvements into
shipyard operations. Through Technology Focus Teams (TFTs), the program targets solutions in areas such as asset visibility, operational IT, unmanned systems,
extended reality, robotic process automation, advanced manufacturing, inspection and testing, and corrosion control and repair. These efforts enhance workforce
productivity, improve maintenance execution, and contribute to reduced ship availability durations, where delays can cost approximately $1M per day. Sustained funding
is required to support additional projects, initiatives, and implementation of successful capabilities across Naval Shipyard operations.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions, Article Quantities in Each)                                                             FY 2027 FY 2027 FY 2027
                                                                                                                   FY 2025 FY 2026           Base    OOC     Total
Title: Advanced Shipyard Technology                                                                                   4.156   3.600            1.710   0.000   1.710
                                                                                                         Articles:       -       -                -       -        -
FY 2026 Plans:
This technology area will remain a primary focus for implementation in FY 2026.
Robotic Process Automation (RPA)
Continue development, evaluation, and implementation of RPA solutions to improve operational efficiency and
reduce manual administrative and data-processing tasks within Naval Shipyard operations. Focus on high-value
automation opportunities and integrating mature solutions into standard workflows.
FY 2027 Base Plans:

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions, Article Quantities in Each)                                                           FY 2027     FY 2027      FY 2027
                                                                                                                   FY 2025    FY 2026      Base        OOC          Total
Continue maturation and implementation of RPA capabilities, expanding automation solutions that enhance
operational efficiency, reduce manual workload, and support improved data management across shipyard
processes.
FY 2027 OOC Plans:
N/A
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The decrease from $3.6M in FY26 to $1.710M in FY27 reflects the transition of the Technology Focus Teams
(TFTs) from the establishment and development phase to the sustainment and implementation phase, shifting
