A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Advanced Shipyard Technology (AST) program supports Navy efforts to address warfighter maintenance and construction challenges by developing, maturing,
and demonstrating technologies that improve Naval Shipyard sustainment operations. AST aligns with priorities outlined in the CNO Navigation Plan 2025, which
emphasizes improving fleet readiness and accelerating the integration of robotics, autonomy, and digital capabilities across Navy operational and sustainment
environments.

AST funding facilitates collaboration between government, academia, and industry to rapidly prototype and transition technology and process improvements into
shipyard operations. Through Technology Focus Teams (TFTs), the program targets solutions in areas such as asset visibility, operational IT, unmanned systems,
extended reality, robotic process automation, advanced manufacturing, inspection and testing, and corrosion control and repair. These efforts enhance workforce
productivity, improve maintenance execution, and contribute to reduced ship availability durations, where delays can cost approximately $1M per day. Sustained funding
is required to support additional projects, initiatives, and implementation of successful capabilities across Naval Shipyard operations.

