INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$0605013BL$$, 2027, $$Systems Modifications and Development
The Defense Contract Management Agency (DCMA) is engaged in several major Information Technology (IT) initiatives to improve and modernize the information
technology environment. IT is the primary enabling capability the acquisition workforce relies upon to communicate with contractors, the Department of War (DOW)
acquisition community and other customers. The National Defense Strategy (NDS) IT modernization efforts drive these initiatives.

 The DCMA continues to execute an IT modernization strategy established to improve visibility, insight, and collaboration between DCMA, the Military Departments
 (MILDEPs), other Defense Agencies and DOD Field Activities (DAFAs), other federal agencies, and contractors in the Defense Industrial Base (DIB). Core to this
 strategy is the Modernization and Analytics Initiative (MAI) program to modernize and integrate the entire DCMA portfolio of aging Contract Administration Services
 (CAS) capabilities and supporting infrastructure, leveraging Platform and Software as a Service (PaaS/SaaS) cloud environment, the Defense Logistics Agency (DLA)
 Procurement Integrated Enterprise Environment (PIEE), the Department of the Navy (DON) Product Data Reporting and Evaluation Program (PDREP), and Advancing
 Analytics (ADVANA) Business Intelligence and Data Analytics platform to enable departmentwide CAS capabilities.

 These efforts support the Director’s strategic objective to modernize CAS tools to improve DCMA processes, enhance DOW Acquisition insights, and standardize
 contract administration actions and data accessibility across the Department enterprise.

 Development and research initiatives are core components of the DCMA ability to align efforts appropriately to the DOW IT strategy. In FY 2027, the DCMA continues to
 invest in the PIEE (hosts Wide Area WorkfFlow (WAWF) and Electronic Data Access (EDA).

 This core initiative will empower mobile and fixed users' ability to utilize DOW enterprise capabilities at the same level with improved efficiency and effectiveness. The
 DCMA aligns with the DOW strategy for software modernization of enterprise capabilities. This involves migrating the DCMA application infrastructure to enterprise
 hosting environments and modern technology platforms, rationalizing existing applications to ensure capabilities align with mission requirements, and adopting new
 DOW strategies for modern software development methodologies. These solutions will improve process gaps to streamline/simplify automated contract administration,
 provide real-time data visibility, reduce manual intervention, and provide effective, regulatory-based tools for use across the Department.

 Blue List
 In support of DOW’s Drone Dominance, the Blue List is an ecosystem our US Government, and industry partners, providing an aggregated list of compliant Unmanned
 Aerial System (UAS) platforms and components. The Blue list will expand functionality to create a Blue Marketplace for efficient purchasing, integrate auto-designed
aircraft software, foster a community knowledge hub, scale to include all Unmanned System (UxS) domains, additive and subtractive manufacturing hardware and
 conduct compliance assessments.$$, $$Development and research initiatives are a core component in the DCMA ability to align efforts appropriately to the DOW IT advancement strategy. The DCMA
aligns with the DOW strategy for software modernization of enterprise capabilities. This involves migrating the DCMA application infrastructure to enterprise hosting
environments and modern technology platforms, rationalizing existing applications to ensure capabilities align with mission requirements, and adopting new DOW
strategies for modern software development methodologies. This will ensure delivery of secure, interoperable, and optimized solutions. To meet the needs of the DOW
community, the DCMA is dedicated to developing and implementing its IT modernization strategy.

 The Blue List platform, designated as Defense Business System (DBS), is the definitive materiel solution. It will function as DOW's single, authoritative digital ecosystem
 for the entire life cycle of commercial UAS acquisition. It will directly enable the goals of DOW’s Drone Dominance by providing a trusted, vetted, and streamlined
 marketplace that empowers warfighters while ensuring enterprise-wide compliance and security.

