A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Development and research initiatives are a core component in the DCMA ability to align efforts appropriately to the DOW IT advancement strategy. The DCMA
aligns with the DOW strategy for software modernization of enterprise capabilities. This involves migrating the DCMA application infrastructure to enterprise hosting
environments and modern technology platforms, rationalizing existing applications to ensure capabilities align with mission requirements, and adopting new DOW
strategies for modern software development methodologies. This will ensure delivery of secure, interoperable, and optimized solutions. To meet the needs of the DOW
community, the DCMA is dedicated to developing and implementing its IT modernization strategy.

 The Blue List platform, designated as Defense Business System (DBS), is the definitive materiel solution. It will function as DOW's single, authoritative digital ecosystem
 for the entire life cycle of commercial UAS acquisition. It will directly enable the goals of DOW’s Drone Dominance by providing a trusted, vetted, and streamlined
 marketplace that empowers warfighters while ensuring enterprise-wide compliance and security.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                        FY 2025          FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: System Modifications Development                                                                                                        4.546            1.192         1.190
Description: The DCMA uses the system and modifications program for its IT modernization strategy.

The MAI program utilizes commercial innovations such as Platform as a Service (PaaS), Software as a Service (SaaS), artificial
intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) with cost-effective solutions. It ensures future contract management oversight
to the DOW base by: (i) aligning to the DOW IT Strategy for Software Modernization, DOW Cloud Computing efforts, and
investing in next-generation Infrastructure while ensuring secure supply chains (ii) supporting the Strategic Plan for Defense
Wide Procurement Capabilities and implementing a robust environment that enables development of enterprise solutions and
environment to enhance the DCMA CAS mission. This approach promotes the tenets of reusable code, pre-built applications, a
no code/low code environment, and industry developed solutions that can ride on the same platform. This enterprise environment
will encompass data analytics across multiple sources and enable business-process driven citizen development of low code
applications to provide DOW instantaneous and dynamic business insight of contract management data.

PIEE is an existing DBS that provides an IT platform of enterprise services, capabilities, and systems grouped into modules
with the objective of seamlessly supporting the end-to-end Procure-to-Pay (P2P) business processes for the DOW. Leveraging
role-based access, PIEE provides users with access to many of the critical enterprise capabilities used every day by hundreds

