Title: Mobility                                                                                                                      3.921       3.851         3.958
Description: The Mobility Program delivers secure, enterprise-level mobile capabilities that enable the Department of War (DoW)
to operate with speed, resilience, and global reach. The program provides integrated, end-to-end mobile solutions that allow
DoW civilians, military personnel, and mission partners to securely access unclassified and classified information and mission
applications from modern mobile devices. These services directly support warfighter readiness, senior leader decision-making,
and distributed operations across Combatant Commands, the Military Services, Defense Agencies, and Field Activities.

The Mobility Program provides the core enterprise infrastructure including mobile device management, identity and access
control, secure mobility gateways, and Zero Trust aligned endpoint protections required to safeguard DoW information in
contested and evolving threat environments. This capability enables mobile users to securely authenticate, communicate,
collaborate, and access operational data regardless of location.

FY 2026 Plans:
• Initiate limited fielding of the new tethered classified mobility solution for select DoW mission partners.
• Investigate and implement enhancements to the Commercial Solutions for Classified (CSfC) architecture, including adoption of
a layered security framework, modernization of components to meet updated NSA cybersecurity standards and emerging protocol
requirements, and expansion of CSfC service options to support rapid deployment of secure classified communications.
• Integrate enterprise mobile data lose prevention (DLP) controls into DISA-managed mobility platforms to prevent unauthorized
data access, transfer, or exfiltration across DoW mobile devices and applications.
• Deploy digital data rights management (DRM) protections enabling granular control of data usage (view, share, forward, copy/
paste, screenshot restrictions) to ensure sensitive information remains protected when acceded on mobile endpoints.



