B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                 FY 2025       FY 2026       FY 2027
• Conduct operational demonstrations with Combatant Commands and mission partners to validate Cross Domain Mobility (CDM)
capability, alignment with security policies, and interoperability with existing enterprise platforms.
• Conduct 5G mobility pilot assessment to evaluate next-generation wireless technologies.
FY 2027 Plans:
• Conduct technical assessments of mobile text messaging platforms to determine appropriate policy, technical feasibility, and
compliance pathways for retaining, auditing, and securely storing mobile text communications across DoW-managed mobility
platform.
• Assess mobile gateway modernization needs to enable Enterprise Gray adoption at scale, including enhancements to routing,
VPN services, encryption modules, logging, and traffic inspection capabilities required to secure mobile communications across
gray transport channels.
• Pilot deployment of AI-driven mobile threat defense (MTD) to detect anomalous device behavior.
• Deploy advanced application-vetting and threat detection tools integrated with mobile device platforms to strengthen mobile
cybersecurity protections.
• Enhance Commercial Solutions for Classified (CSfC) capabilities by finalizing layered security architecture designs, completing
compliance upgrades with updated NSA security standards, and conducting field tests for rapid deployment toolkits.
