INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$0604551BR$$, 2027, $$Catapult is a private cloud technology-based data analytics platform that provides a continuously augmented, real-time repository of data ingested from a variety of
sources including government agencies, combatant commands, intelligence reports and open sources. The Catapult data lake and web-based software tool suite are
adaptable to any National Defense Strategy (NDS) mission problem set and provide leading-edge capabilities for data and information discovery, access, aggregation,
correlation, visualization, analysis, sharing, and distribution for users across the Whole-of-Government - DOW, Interagency, and Intelligence Community (IC) Partners -
with Secret Internet Protocol Router Network (SIPRNet) or Joint World-Wide Intelligence Communications System (JWICS) access at no cost to end users.$$, $$This project enables the Defense Threat Reduction Agency's (DTRA’s) Catapult Information System program of record to design, develop, test and deliver mission
capabilities that support the ability to aggregate and analyze data on global emerging threats, threat actors and threat networks. Catapult allows DTRA to develop,
engineer, test and deploy analytical tools, data science methodologies and software applications in support of the warfighter. Catapult and its web-based suite of
software tools integrate data sources that support the detection and identification of emerging threats, threat networks and actors, command and control, operations, and
engagement for neutralizing, attacking and defeating both current and emerging counter weapons of mass destruction (CWMD) threats.
Catapult uses its RDT&E funding to meet user needs using tools and services that reside in Catapult, a cloud technology-based data analytics platform developed and
delivered by DTRA. Catapult provides an extensible continuously augmented, near real-time updated data analytic platform of information regarding threats and threat
networks along with a set of discovery, access, aggregation, correlation, analysis and sharing tools and services. Catapult is fully operational and accredited on the
Secret Internet Protocol Router Network (SIPRNet) and Joint Worldwide Intelligence Communications System (JWICS). Catapult integrates cutting-edge technologies,
including machine learning and AI, to enhance data ingestion, processing, and analysis while leveraging DTRA’s enterprise DevSecOps platform that provides agile path
to production environments, a standardized and automated tool chain that supports continuous integration/continuous delivery, and well-defined governance processes.

This project achieves transformational mission capabilities and postures the Agency to meet emerging mission requirements through innovative technology solutions
and service upgrades.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                    FY 2025           FY 2026     FY 2027
Title: RA: CWMD Cross-Cutting Technical and Information Sciences                                                                           7.290             3.992       7.500
Description: This project enables DTRA’s Catapult Information System program to develop dynamic data analytic, data
visualizations, and Artificial Intelligence (AI) enabled applications for combat support, and to expand robust data ingestion
pipelines to include ingesting multi-modal data sources across diverse networks. The Catapult program creates new emerging
threat data analytics supporting global DoW mission partners and deploys Generative AI powered capabilities that enable CWMD
Pathway Defeat.

FY 2026 Plans:

                                                                               ON SYSTEM                                    TECHNICAL AND INFORMATION
                                                                                                                            SCIENCES

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                FY 2025    FY 2026      FY 2027
- Optimize the Catapult Data Platform including analysis of Cloudera data platform alternatives and migration assessment,
catapult framework improvements to add additional data types to the Catapult data lake and enhance catapult capabilities
providing text translation and optical character recognition for catapult data, and implement prioritized work streams to enable
mission specific use cases in isolated, secure Data Zones for exploration and analysis.
- Expand advanced data science capabilities including large language model ontology processing improvements, metadata
tagging enhancements and natural language processing as a service.
- Innovate data analysis and data visualization capabilities providing updated common Countering Weapons of Mass Destruction/
Chemical, Biological, Radiological, and Nuclear information visualization from Catapult data lake feeds, advanced grouping
visuals, and geospatial search enhancements.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Complete cloud migration on Non-classified Internet Protocol Router Network (NIPR) and extend and migrate Catapult on the
DTRA Data Platform Secret Internet Protocol Router Network (SIPR) cloud.
- Improve Catapult framework to enable multi-modal large language model (LLM) computer vision and characterization of imagery,
audio and video.
- Develop and field LLM foreign text translation and optical character recognition for Catapult data.
- Enable Artificial Intelligence augmented computer vision capabilities for text-based search of images, audio and video.
- Expand advanced data science capabilities including LLM ontology processing improvements, metadata tagging enhancements
and natural language processing as a service capability.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The current President’s Budget request is an increase from the previous fiscal year. The increase is due to a realignment of
funds from Budget Activity 5/0605141BR to reinvest funding in the DoW Program of Record, Catapult, and combine Agency data
initiatives to advance data and knowledge management efforts.
