FY 2026 Plans:
FY 2026 program plans include the following Counter Weapons of Mass Destruction projects ($15.192M)
- Integrate artificial intelligence (AI) into CWMD operations to achieve efficiency and superiority for the warfighter. ($2M)
- Accelerate the development and deployment of biomanufacturing (BIO) solutions to support critical missions. Develop bio-based
alternatives for critical chemicals, minerals, and energetics that are qualified for use in warfighting systems. ($1M)
- Advance novel technologies, including quantum sensing in non-kinetic operations, to advance capabilities for the maintenance of
communications and control in degraded or denied conditions. ($1M)
- Develop technologies that demonstrate capabilities to detect, identify, and mitigate weapons of mass destruction. ($3.19M)
- Develop Nuclear Plume Advisory Algorithms to demonstrate on simulated scenes for use in satellite products. ($2M)
- Develop computational modeling tools to reconstruct heavy weapon repeated firing events in combat scenarios to quantify
blast exposure and risk injury scores to service members; enable accurate prediction of blast dose from a single exposure and
cumulative blast dose from repeated exposures encountered during prolonged firing in combat operations. ($2M)
- Research and develop applications of nanoelectromechanical systems towards the development of ultracompact handheld-sized
airborne contamination monitoring systems. ($2M)
- Develop synthetic and game environments for information resilience training and exercises to understand and mitigate foreign
malign influence. ($1M)
- Research technologies to enable real-time streaming of radiation sensor data in subsea (underwater) environments. ($1M)
FY 2027 Plans:

