Note
This program element supports the development of a series of advanced analytic efforts to more effectively identify risks and threats to Surge Layer Defense and, more
broadly, the Department of War's (DoW’s) Mission Assurance (MA) as identified in the current National Defense Strategy (NDS).

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Beginning in FY 2023, the Defense Threat Reduction Agency (DTRA), as the DoW Center of Excellence for Mission Assurance Assessments, was tasked by the Deputy
Assistant Secretary of War for Defense Continuity and Mission Assurance to provide oversight and program management of the Critical Infrastructure Defense Analysis
Center (CIDAC) program in coordination with the Office of the Under Secretary of War for Policy (OUSW(P)), the U.S. Navy, and the U.S. Air Force. In FY 2027, this
mission responsibility and funding transferred from DTRA to the Office of the Deputy Assistant Secretary of the Navy for Installations and Facilities DASN(I&F).

