D. Acquisition Strategy
The Family of Special Operations Vehicles (FSOV) has been designated a Major Capability Acquisition (MCA) at Milestone C, in accordance with the authority in DoD
Directive 5135.02 and the guidance in DoD Instruction 5000.85.

 FOSOV utilizes the MCA ACAT III acquisition pathway to acquire capabilities to support global operations in diverse environments with varying threat levels for
 survivability, autonomy, lethality, signature management, mobility/performance, communications, and product development, incorporated across the FSOV family of
 vehicles to include: Ground Mobility Vehicle (GMV 1.1 / (Infantry Squad Vehicle (ISV)); Non-Standard Commercial Vehicle (NSCV); Lightweight Tactical All-Terrain
 Vehicle (LTATV); Mine Resistant Ambush Protected (MRAP) Vehicle; Armored round Mobility System (AGMS) and SOF Mods on other service common platforms such
 as the ISV, JLTV and Squad Multipurpose Equipment Transport (SMET).




