Congressional Add: Combatant Craft Heavy Vessel Design Improvements                                                         -         7.500
FY 2026 Plans: Combatant Craft Heavy Vessel Design Improvements – Contract vehicles are in place to
develop and test two prototype low-tide yard carts to validate new launch and recovery procedures for the
Combatant Craft Heavy (CCH). The objective of this testing is to prove a significant increase in the CCH's
operational window, which is currently restricted by tidal cycles. Funding will also be used to evaluate and
implement design improvements that could be used to retrofit fielded CCH vessels, ensuring the platform meets
or exceeds operational requirements in critical areas of operation.
