INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$0604826J$$, 2027, $$Joint C5 Capability Development, Integration, and Interoperability Assessments program leads Command, Control, Communications, Computers, and Cyber (C5)
assessments, analyses, capability development, and Joint Fires Command and Control (C2) interoperability efforts required to achieve an effective, integrated, and
interoperable combined joint force. Efforts include C5 requirements determination, architectures development and integration, data and standards, integration, Allies
and coalition integration and interoperability assessments, and Joint Fires C2 interoperability coordinating firepower compatibility.

 The Joint Staff leads the Department of War’s effort to develop and integrate the Combined Joint All-Domain Command and Control (CJADC2) across the Department.
 The Joint C5 program is the Joint Staff focal point for this responsibility. Its projects provide the research, analysis, and execution needed to make the CJADC2 strategy
 a reality.$$, $$Counter-small Unmanned Aircraft Systems (C-sUAS) efforts will demonstrate and support advance prototype efforts with technologies and concepts to enable and/or
accelerate their transition to acquisition programs. The efforts will address technical gaps between initial technologies or concept development and quickly transition to
warfighter capabilities. Efforts will explore new concepts and their applications in potential future operating environments within a systems-of-systems context. These
joint advanced prototyping efforts will inform future requirements and support Military Services' acquisition strategy planning to address the evolving s-UAS threats and
new environments to which C-sUAS must be deployed.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                        FY 2025           FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: C-sUAS Prototyping New Joint Capabilities                                                                                                  -                 -        580.348
Description: Execute testing, demonstrations, and operational assessments of new C-sUAS technology to explore new concepts,
new applications of existing systems, and new industry technologies. New concepts and technologies demonstrations will address
future capability gaps to maintain pace with evolving current & threats and employment environments.

FY 2027 Plans:
JIATF 401 will pursue the acceleration of a layered defeat portfolio, including options to ensure the protection of critical assets
across diverse operational environments. Our approach is system-agnostic, focused on identifying and integrating the most
effective capabilities to meet operational needs by addressing each stage of the kill chain, rather than committing to specific
platforms or vendors. To maintain tactical overmatch against evolving threats, FY 2027 funding will focus on the following areas:

Rapid Development & Acceleration – Supports the rapid development of C-sUAS defeat options to ensure protection across
diverse operational environments.

Advanced Tech Assessments - Supports the rapid operational assessment of commercial technologies and the "lab-to-field"
pipeline. Critical for testing C-sUAS systems against emerging threats prior to procurement.

Tactical C2 & Architecture Integration - Supports the software development and systems engineering required to establish
common air domain awareness. Supports the system-agnostic integration of advanced decision aids.

                                                                              ed Aircraft Systems

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                             FY 2025    FY 2026          FY 2027
Common Testing, Demonstrations & Joint Exercises - Supports DoW-wide C-sUAS exercises, testing, and demonstrations
of emerging prototypes, integration of sensors, common tactical C2, and effectors to ensure seamless, accelerated reaction
times across the entire kill chain. Leverages commercially available, system-agnostic technologies and advanced decision aids
to validate mission-ready capabilities against emerging threats. Supports executing large-scale exercises to ensure C-sUAS
solutions are fully interoperable across DoW components and established common air domain architectures.

Funds will be executed on JIATF 401 priorities and emerging trends.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increase from FY 2026 to FY 2027 reflects the additional resourcing by the DoW to support the establishment of the JIATF 401.
