A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Project 001 C5 Assessments and Analyses. This project leads analysis and assessment of Combined Joint All-Domain Command and Control (CJADC2) for the
Department of War. The findings from this project guide resource allocation and operational decisions to improve warfighter effectiveness and interoperability, with all
efforts directly aligned with top priorities of the Chairman of the Joint Chief of Staff, the Secretary of War Analysis Plans, and Combatant Command’s CJADC2 priorities
and Tier I exercises and experiment activities.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                       FY 2025          FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: C5 Assessments and Analyses                                                                                                            8.512            7.459         7.887
Description: Support the Chairman’s statutory requirement to advise the Secretary of War (SECWAR) on development of Joint
Command, Control, Communications and Cyber (C5) capability, including the design, integration and interoperability of such
capabilities through requirements, integrated architectures, data standards and assessments. The staff supports the Chairman's
focus area of improving Joint and Combined warfighting capability and the Secretary's line of effort to strengthen alliances and
attract new partners. Interoperability is assessed and integrated solutions are developed to improve CJADC2 and C5 system
performance by providing recommendations based on operational architectures and evolving standards and data products.

