B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                      FY 2025     FY 2026        FY 2027

C5 Architectures - Build upon the successes of prior years to mature and expand C5 Architectures. Continue to lead the delivery
of architecture, mission thread, and analysis products to support Chairman's directed focus areas, CJADC2 initiatives, and key
programmatic reviews (Integrated Acquisition Portfolio Reviews, Technology Modernization Reviews, Strategic Portfolio Reviews,
and Capability Portfolio Reviews). The focus will shift to enterprise-wide implementation, ensuring full compliance and integration.

Efforts will concentrate on enhancing and expanding the authoritative repository for architecture and mission thread data,
leveraging it as a cornerstone for advanced analysis and data-driven decision-making. This includes maturing capabilities for
discovery, accessibility, and reuse to enable seamless integration with North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), Coalition,
and FVEY partners' data, building on the established leadership within NATO and FVEY forums. Continue to refine and maintain
the Joint Common Service/System Function List and Warfighter Mission Area Architecture Development Standards, actively
identifying gaps and opportunities to improve integration and interoperability. In partnership with FVEY members, continue
developing mission threads that support the FVEY Strategy to Compete Implementation Plan, focusing on areas of mutual
strategic advantage.

Data and Standards improves joint and combined warfighter interoperability—enhancing joint force readiness—by developing
and maintaining data policies, standards, and governance structures; integrating them into capability requirements; facilitating
implementation through rapid prototyping, integration, and evaluation of emerging technologies and data solutions in joint
and coalition environments; and providing subject matter expertise to Combatant Commands and Joint Staff J6 divisions to
ensure mission priorities are supported with operationally ready, standards-compliant data capabilities. Serve as the Joint Staff
Office of Primary Responsibility for the development, coordination, and maintenance of interoperable command and control
data exchange, tactical interoperability standards, message text formats, symbology, data management practices, information
exchange requirements, tactical data link standards, NATO Standardization Agreements, and related documentation to support
joint, interagency, coalition, and mission partner operations.

Facilitate Implementation through Rapid Prototyping, Integration, and Evaluation

Identify, prioritize, lead, and participate in operational experiments, demonstrations, and technical evaluations to assess
warfighter-related data exchanges and tactical interoperability standards across joint, interagency, and coalition communities.
Capture lessons learned and provided recommendations to advance C4/cyber data exchange and tactical interoperability
standards in support of warfighter requirements.



