readiness reports, focusing on complex, multi-domain scenarios and validating the integration of critical warfighting functions (e.g.,
Joint Fires, Contested Logistics) into the CJADC2 operational baseline. Mature the architecture repository into an on-demand
analytical service for the Joint Staff and partners. Lead the formal assessment in accordance with the Chairman of the Joint
Chiefs of Staff Manual 8411.01 Development of Warfighting Mission Area Architectures for implementation, delivering an annual
compliance report with data-driven recommendations to refine Warfighter Mission Area standards. As the U.S. lead for North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) and FVEY architecture teams, spearhead joint architecture efforts to validate standards and
deliver formal reports on interoperability gaps to guide future coalition investment.

