A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Joint Staff Analytical Support (JSAS) family of programs provide defense analytical support capabilities for the Joint Staff and Combatant Commands (CCMDs).
JSAS encompasses tools and infrastructure required to conduct analyses and formulate results that assist the Chairman in fulfilling his statutory responsibilities.
A primary focus of this analysis is the development of the operational concepts that guide the evolution of the Joint Force. This effort is led by the threat-informed
Joint Warfighting Concept (JWC), an overarching framework that is detailed through subordinate Concepts of Operation (CONOPS) and Concepts of Employment
(CONEMPs). These integrated concepts describe how the force will fight and drive the identification of Concept-Required Capabilities (CRCs). This ensures that the
entire JWC family of concepts provides direct, traceable input to the Joint Force Requirements Process (JFRP), aids senior leader decision-making, and implements
timely, low-cost Joint Force development initiatives.

